%N A397613 Decimal expansion of the small face angle, in radians, of a canonical (dual-uniform) hexagonal trapezohedron.
%C A397613 The hexagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the hexagonal antiprism.
%C A397613 Its faces are kites with one acute angle (this constant) and three obtuse angles (A397614).
%H A397613 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397613/b397613.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A397613 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HexagonalTrapezohedron.html">Hexagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
